ers%20to%20the%20first%20phase%20of%2021%20days%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lockdown%20would%20be%20extended%20several%20times%20and%20imposed%20with%20different%20levels%20of%20severity%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20state%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20a%20reference%20to%20the%202002%20zombie-apocalypse%20horror%20film%20%3Cem%3E28%20Days%20Later%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Directed%20by%20Danny%20Boyle%2C%20it%20stars%20Cillian%20Murphy%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgoldenglobes%2Fstatus%2F1744188296090263783%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgoldenglobes%2Fstatus%2F1744188296090263783%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1Z0dvSWFM7KHXgC2vaFj6G%5C%22%3Erecently%20won%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Golden%20Globe%20for%20his%20performance%20in%20the%20biopic%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20a%20survivor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMhatre%E2%80%99s%20poem%20is%20also%20about%20surviving%20the%20pandemic%2C%20reuniting%20with%20loved%20ones%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20period%20of%20uncertainty%20and%20anxiety%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20planes%20take%20off%20in%20a%20unified%20choir%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhere%20to%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20ask%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20each%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-one%20days%20dissolve%20in%20an%20embrace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20still%20waiting%20for%20you%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20Day%20One%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eat%20the%20airport%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20stanza%20of%20the%20poem%20is%20a%20reaffirmation%20of%20the%20renewal%20of%20the%20planet%20and%20everyone%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20when%20the%20pandemic%20entered%20our%20lives%2C%20poets%20around%20the%20world%20have%20tried%20to%20respond%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20not%20always%20with%20great%20success.%20An%20anthology%2C%20%3Cem%3ETogether%20in%20a%20Sudden%20Strangeness%3A%20America%E2%80%99s%20Poets%20Respond%20to%20the%20Pandemic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20edited%20by%20Alice%20Quinn%2C%20former%20poetry%20editor%20of%3Cem%3E%20The%20New%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20published%20in%20late%202020%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F14%2Fbooks%2Freview-together-in-sudden-strangeness-pandemic-poetry-alice-quinn.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F14%2Fbooks%2Freview-together-in-sudden-strangeness-pandemic-poetry-alice-quinn.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3d9HFrUZN3LZU4j5GIiWVx%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20faltering%20%E2%80%9Con%20every%20front%E2%80%9D.%20Despite%20a%20few%20misses%2C%20however%2C%20poetry%20did%20prove%20to%20be%20therapeutic%20%E2%80%94%20with%20even%20mental%20health%20professionals%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F12%2Fwell%2Fmind%2Fnational-poetry-month-coronavirus.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F12%2Fwell%2Fmind%2Fnational-poetry-month-coronavirus.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1hnGcmJOR9q7iEr8lA8GOj%5C%22%3Eadvising%20their%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20clients%20to%20read%20more%20verse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20too%2C%20several%20poets%20have%20responded%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20their%20own%20survival%20or%20loss.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20books%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20pandemic%20in%20India%20was%20%3Cem%3ESinging%20in%20the%20Dark%3A%20A%20Global%20Anthology%20of%20Poetry%20Under%20Lockdown%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2020)%3Cem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eedited%20by%20K.%20Satchidanandan%20and%20Nishi%20Chawla.%20(I%20had%20also%20contributed%20a%20few%20poems%20to%20it.)%20Nikita%20Parik%E2%80%99s%20powerful%20collection%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcrows-nikita-parik-poetry-review%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcrows-nikita-parik-poetry-review%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0SI2nkFIGGCIJTXMPPlk0a%5C%22%3EMy%20City%20is%20Murder%20of%20Crows%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E(2022)%2C%20addresses%20the%20cocktails%20of%20emotions%20sparked%20by%20surviving%20the%20deadly%20second%20wave%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Vinita%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Natural%20Language%20of%20Grief%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20also%20bears%20witness%20to%20the%20ravages%20of%20the%20disease.%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20suitable%20addition%20to%20this%20rich%20and%20growing%20body%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20titular%20poem%20of%20the%20book%20refers%20to%20the%20sirens%20of%20ambulances%20taking%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20mother%20%E2%80%94%20Aai%2C%20in%20Marathi%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20hospital%20after%20she%20is%20detected%20with%20stage-three%20cancer%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20rain-kissed%20day%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Esirens%20from%20ambulances%20wring%20at%20full%20volume%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Esending%20a%20shockwave%20through%20this%20somnolence%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ethe%20city%20has%20been%20suddenly%20diagnosed%20with%20Stage%203C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20image%20of%20the%20murder%20is%20fused%20with%20the%20image%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20the%20breathless%20lines%20of%20the%20poem%20follow%20each%20other%2C%20without%20as%20much%20as%20a%20comma%2C%20like%20machine%20gun%20fire.%20Medical%20terms%20make%20too%20frequent%20appearances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Enow%2C%20water%20levels%20are%20rising%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eher%20stomach%20bloats%20with%20a%20spell%20of%20monsoon%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eand%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20omental%20biopsy%20in%20sight%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eno%20cytology%20report%20collected%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20has%20ever%20served%20as%20a%20caregiver%20will%20provide%20testimony%20to%20the%20sheer%20anxiety%20of%20waiting%20for%20hours%20in%20cold%20waiting%20rooms%20of%20hospitals%20and%20nursing%20homes%2C%20for%20medical%20reports%2C%20treatment%2C%20for%20tests.%20This%20poem%20examines%20the%20contours%20of%20bereavement%2C%20which%20sometimes%20begins%20with%20a%20diagnosis%2C%20long%20before%20the%20actual%20event%20of%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20introduction%20to%20this%20book%2C%20dedicated%20to%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20he%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CShe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20Stage%203C%20Ovarian%20Cancer.%20I%20could%20feel%20the%20voice%20of%20sirens%2C%20the%20constant%20beat%20of%20cardiograms%20filling%20up%20my%20veins%20as%20my%20father%20broke%20the%20news%20to%20me.%20From%20then%2C%20the%20sound%20of%20sirens%20became%20second%20nature.%20Synchronised%20to%20my%20heartbeat.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20sound%20of%20sirens%20is%20not%20only%20the%20bugle%20of%20fear%20and%20loss%3B%20it%20can%20also%20be%20a%20sound%20of%20hope.%20As%20Mhatre%20reports%2C%20his%2093-year-old%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20recovery%20from%20Covid-19%20became%20a%20story%20of%20hope%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20sound%20of%20sirens%20was%20celebrating%20our%20survival.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeath%20has%20served%20as%20an%20inspiration%20to%20poets%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGilgamesh%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGilgamesh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20written%20some%204%2C000%20years%20ago.%20But%20not%20every%20expression%20of%20death%20and%20loss%20%E2%80%94%20and%20survival%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20epic.%20Even%20in%20its%20most%20quotidian%20expressions%2C%20it%20can%20provide%20relief%2C%20hope%2C%20and%20catharsis.%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20book%20does%20succeed%20in%20doing%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUttaran%20Das%20Gupta%20is%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20writer%20and%20journalist.%20He%20teaches%20journalism%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20Sonipat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fof-poems-pandemics-and-death%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sanket%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20collection%20of%20poems%20reflects%20on%20a%20city%20in%20the%20grip%20of%20Covid-19%2C%20but%20also%20celebrates%20surviving%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fof-poems-pandemics-and-death%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20high-value%20Russian%20planes%20'shot%20down'%2C%20Ukraine%20claims%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-a-50-ukraine-russia-plane_6422378.jpg%3F20240115135431%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20high-value%20Russian%20aircraft%20have%20been%20shot%20down%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20claimed%2C%20in%20what%20would%20be%20a%20major%20blow%20to%20its%20air%20force.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Across%20the%20World%2C%20Monarchs%20Continue%20to%20Reign%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3